      "title": "Part 1: Installation",
      "id": "https://importantimport.github.io/lume_theme_shiraha/articles/part-1-installation/",
      "url": "https://importantimport.github.io/lume_theme_shiraha/articles/part-1-installation/",
      "content_html": "<h2>Setup Deno &#x26; Lume</h2>\n<p>As this is a Lume theme, please follow the <a href=\"https://deno.com/manual@v1.34.2/getting_started/installation\">Deno installation instructions</a> and <a href=\"https://lume.land/docs/overview/installation/\">Lume documentation</a> to install them first.</p>\n<h2>Install Lume Theme Shiraha</h2>\n<p>Now that you should have a basic Lume blog, modify <code>_config.ts</code> to use the Shiraha theme:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-diff\"><div class=\"highlight-header\"><div class=\"highlight-language\">diff</div><div class=\"highlight-caption\">_config.ts</div></div><pre><code tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">1</span>import lume from 'lume/mod.ts'</span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">2</span><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+ import lts from 'https://deno.land/x/lume_theme_shiraha/mod.ts'</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">3</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">4</span><span class=\"pl-md\">- const site = lume()</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">5</span><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+ const site = lume().use(lts())</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">6</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line-number\" aria-hidden=\"true\">7</span>export default site</span>\n</code></pre></div>"
    }
  ]
